A student's test score can be any real number between 0 and 100. The intent of the following class is to print a student's score as a letter grade.

public class TestReport {
    private double score;

    public TestReport(double value) {
        score = value;
    }

    public void printGrade() {
        if (score >= 90.0)
            System.out.println("Congratulations!");
        if (score >= 80.0)
            System.out.println("Good job.");
        if (score >= 70.0)
            System.out.println("Average score.");
        if (score >= 60.0)
            System.out.println("Barely passing.");
        if (score < 60.0)
            System.out.println("Failing score.");
    }
}

Consider the following segment of a client program.

TestReport t = new TestReport(testScore);
t.printGrade();

If testScore is 75.0, what will be output?
